	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmm... as a Ranger, different situations calls for different weapons. For sheer DPS, always keep the fastest weapon in your primary hand (to take advantage of the damage bonus), and your best ratio weapon in your off-hand (Damage bonus does not apply so delay is not that big of a priority).<br><br>So, if you're grouped with competant tanks or you want to dish out damage (like SKs and Paladins who can out-taunt you), go with Defiance (main), and either the Centi or the Venomous (the proc will probably give you better taunt) in your off-hand.<br><br>However, if you're grouped with an incompetant tank, or you don't want to draw too much agro, switch to Wurmslayer in your primary (slow delay sucks but can still do some damage), and again either a Centi or the Venomous depending how much taunt you want.<br><br>If you have Defiance, don't bother with the Lamentation.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Mar 10 19:44:50 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>**********************************<br>"<span style='color: red;'>Man who goes to bed with itchy bum, wakes with smelly fingers.</span style='color: red;'>"</td></tr>
